Package com.penthera.virtuososdk

Class Common.Events

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.penthera.virtuososdk.Common.Events
  • Enclosing class:
    Common
    public static final class Common.Events
extends Object
    Identifies Virtuoso's Events, meaning "things that gets reported to the Backplane." Provides helper methods for instantiating Events that Virtuoso reports.

      Internal event for general error reporting, not asset or download specific.

      Reported automatically by the SDK when the asset has been blocked due to errors, and the errors are reset in order to allow the download to continue.

      Identifies that a player has begun local playback of the asset and must be reported by the client using the addPlayStartEvent method.

      Identifies that a player has stopped local playback of the asset and must be reported by the client using the addPlayStopEvent method.

      Reported automatically by the SDK the first time an asset is played through the proxy.
      static String EVENT_QUEUE_FOR_DOWNLOAD
      Reported automatically by the SDK when the user has added a file to the download queue.
      static String EVENT_RESET
      Reported automatically by the SDK after the SDK has handled a remote kill or detected a reinstall of the client app.

      Internal event for error reporting.
      static String EVENT_SUBSCRIBE
      Reported automatically by the SDK after the user has subscribed to receive updates to a feed.
      static String EVENT_UNSUBSCRIBE
      Reported automatically by the SDK after the user has unsubscribed from a feed.

      • addPlayStartEvent

        public static boolean addPlayStartEvent​(Context context,
                                        String assetId,
                                        @Nullable
                                        String assetUuid)
        Creates and automatically saves a Play-Start Event using the provided Context. Include asset Uuid if the asset has been added for download to ensure correct management of expiry. It is optional to allow for recording streaming events.
        Parameters:
        context - Context to use when saving the event
        assetId - Externally provided ID for the asset
        assetUuid - System generated ID for the asset
        Returns:
        True if the event was successfully saved

      • addPlayStartEvent

        public static boolean addPlayStartEvent​(Context context,
                                        String assetId,
                                        @Nullable
                                        String assetUuid,
                                        double timeToFirstFrame)
        Creates and automatically saves a Play-Start Event using the provided Context. Include asset Uuid if the asset has been added for download to ensure correct management of expiry. It is optional to allow for recording streaming events.
        Parameters:
        context - Context to use when saving the event
        assetId - Externally provided ID for the asset
        assetUuid - System generated ID for the asset
        timeToFirstFrame - double value of the time to first frame of video playback
        Returns:
        True if the event was successfully saved

      • addPlayStopEvent

        public static boolean addPlayStopEvent​(Context context,
                                       String assetId,
                                       @Nullable
                                       String assetUuid,
                                       long secondsPlayed)
        Creates and automatically saves a Play-Stop Event using the provided Context.
        Parameters:
        context - The context to use when saving the event
        assetId - Externally provided ID for the asset
        assetUuid - System generated ID for the asset
        secondsPlayed - The amount of time the Asset was played, since the last Play Start Event, in seconds.
        Returns:
        True if the event was successfully saved

      • addCustomEvent

        public static boolean addCustomEvent​(Context context,
                                     String aName,
                                     String assetId,
                                     long data)
        Creates and automatically saves a Custom Event using the provided Context. The Custom Event allows you to create arbitrarily named events and record these events on the Backplane along with the Virtuoso built-in events. This method version takes a long data argument. To send text event data, use the customEvent method.
        Parameters:
        context - Context to use when saving the event
        aName - Name for this custom Event
        assetId - Externally provided ID for the asset
        data - Data to be associated with this Event
        Returns:
        True if the event was successfully saved

      • addCustomEvent

        public static boolean addCustomEvent​(Context context,
                                     String aName,
                                     String assetId,
                                     String data)
        Creates and automatically saves a Custom Event using the provided Context. The Custom Event allows you to create arbitrarily named events and record these events on the Backplane along with the Virtuoso built-in events. This method version takes a String data argument. To send numeric event data, use the customEvent method.
        Parameters:
        context - Context to use when saving the event
        aName - Name for this custom Event
        assetId - Externally provided ID for the asset
        data - Data to be associated with this Event
        Returns:
        True if the event was successfully saved.
